  "contentData": [
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/2804ddfbb019481f996b713ce79e9818",
      "title": "How to start playing your character in D&D",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Tabletop role-playing games are dizzying adventures and a theater of imagination, where you can try on the role of the created hero.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">And a good performance of the character adds dynamics and emotional colors to the game.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">We have put together some important tips on what you can do to improve your game</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/a7af3e47f88b4dcaa2adb956f9d0d3ac",
      "title": " Change your voice!",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Most likely, your character and you are different.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">A man can play a sorceress, and a woman can play a barbarian man.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">So use your voice to indicate when you are speaking and when your character is speaking.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">You don't have to show the wonders of vocals and voice modulation, just come up with a characteristic sound for the character.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">He can speak quickly or slowly, mumble or pick up words, lisp or stutter, whisper or chatter.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/0131647956964dafb1c5fca8b578882d",
      "title": "Describe your character's actions!",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Of course, it's easier to say: \"I'm throwing a fireball!</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">36 damage!” but think about how you do it.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Maybe your character opens a book and recites an ancient spell, or simply snaps his fingers to create an explosion?</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Show events!</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Scream, raging, raise your sword high above the sprawling enemy, pull the string of an imaginary bow.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Convey the movement of the character with your body, indulge in the game (just don't touch your neighbor)!</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/bfbd4de8a9fd4d948e886ccb4e10894f",
      "title": "Describe your character's thoughts!",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Sometimes this may seem unnatural, because in real life we cannot read each other's minds, but in a tabletop role-playing game, such an approach will only add to the spectacle.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">If you see a battlefield littered with bodies, describe the flashback the character has.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Let your hero react to what happens in relation to his worldview and backstory.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Let the herbalist gather flowers, and the paladin protect the weak and infirm.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">React to and interact with the world.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/5c10d7a613fb418f9674d3ec4287face",
      "title": "Pick up ideas from other players!",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Dungeons and Dragons is a team game, and it's not just about combat situations where everyone in the party has a role to play.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">It is interaction with other characters that can truly reveal your character.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Therefore, pick up the ideas of other players, communicate with their characters, be interested in their thoughts and history.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Sometimes a half-hour conversation of the team in a tavern over a mug of ale can be as exciting as a fight with a dragon.</span></p>"
    },
    {
      "contentTypeKey": "ba63b852-9c49-4375-9fb7-770dfd4dccf0",
      "udi": "umb://element/26082f2bf8cd4ba3b0f55315ecacfd11",
      "title": "Work together with the master!",
      "content": "<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">The game master, like no other, is interested in making your character shine like a star in the sky.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Therefore, write a wizard about the background of your character.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">Also ask about the general concept of the game and describe your expectations and wishes.</span> <span class=\"ryNqvb\">The master creates the world in which your hero will live, therefore, having knowledge about the character, he will definitely make his life more interesting, and therefore, will give reasons for a bright play.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span class=\"ryNqvb\">Feel free to try yourself, improvise and create. Have a great game and a great game, villains!</span></p>"
    }
  ],
